      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That's a strong claim. My site manager is a bit of a skeptic, though—he mentioned that some of the newer high-torque models usually dip under 18 hours when you're pushing them hard on concrete. Are you sure about the 24-hour mark for *heavy* use? I'd hate to sign a contract and then have my guys sitting around waiting for charges halfway through a shift.",
